Sentencas: Carbon deposition has a serious effect on the performance of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Parameter study of transient carbon deposition effect on the performance of a planar solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: An unsteady-state 2D model based on COMSOL software is used to study the carbon deposition process in a planar SOFC.
Titulo: Parameter study of transient carbon deposition effect on the performance of a planar solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The carbon deposition, catalyst activity, reaction rate and temperature fields are obtained to analyse the mechanism of carbon deposition in the SOFC at different operating time.
Titulo: Parameter study of transient carbon deposition effect on the performance of a planar solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The effects of the operating voltage, inlet H-2 molar fraction, operating pressure and operating temperature on the performance of the SOFC are investigated in detail.
Titulo: Parameter study of transient carbon deposition effect on the performance of a planar solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: It is found that the biggest variation of the performances caused by carbon deposition occurs in the inlet domain of the anode support layer.
Titulo: Parameter study of transient carbon deposition effect on the performance of a planar solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The increase of operating voltage, inlet H-2 molar fraction, operating pressure and temperature accelerates the carbon deposition process.
Titulo: Parameter study of transient carbon deposition effect on the performance of a planar solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The predicted results could deepen our understanding of carbon deposition and its transient quantitative effects on the catalyst, structure and cell performance.
Titulo: Parameter study of transient carbon deposition effect on the performance of a planar solid oxide fuel cell
